Erlang / IntelliJ / MacOSX
--------------------------

1. brew install elixir
2. brew install rebar3
3. brew cask install intellij and setup ( as instructions )
4. Added plugin for Erlang and setup ( https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/getting-started-with-erlang.html#d279169e315 )
5. Create a project 
6. Consfigure the Project properly with
  * Project SDK should point to Erlang installed 
  * Eg : 
    * Project SDK = Erlang 20
    * SDK home path = /usr/local/Cellar/erlang/20.0.5/lib/erlang
    * classpath = file:///usr/local/Cellar/erlang/20.0.5/lib/erlang/lib
    * sourcepath = file:///usr/local/Cellar/erlang/20.0.5/lib/erlang/lib
    * documentation paths = http://www.erlang.org/documentation/doc-9.0.5
7. That's it